I cannot believe I haven&#39;t reviewed this place yet!? I thought I had. Will have to look back at my food photos. Every time I am in the area, this is my go to place. The last time I was here, we had a large group and waited for an hour. They get busy on a weekend. Plus with a large group... They do not take reservations I was told, so first come first serve. I always get the ahi tuna pesto sandwich be it to done in or to go. Everyone loved their entrees they had, and now they say this I their go to moving forward too. Our waiter was super patient with everyone. Even with the separate checks request by many of the group. There is a parking garage that has a parking app to pay, and I am told around the corner is free parking. There is an outdoor seating area outback and front of you prefer to be outside. There are a lot of vintage decor items too, so take the time to look around. The owner also has a vintage arcade across the street too!! It&#39;s not just one time. I gave it two chances. And both experiences were not pleasant. I would not return or recommend others. The hostess was rude and didn&#39;t care. Even though our party arrived half an hour before they opened the door and second in line, We still waited 20 minutes to get seated. After you are seated, expect another 20 minutes for water, another 20 for ordering food, and don&#39;t expect to get your drinks reordered or water refilled. This experience happened both times with two separate servers.<br>Food is decent. I had the tofu for the first time I was here which was good. But portion is small. <br>This second time I got the salmon was mediocre. Corn nuggets and kimchi cauliflower were mediocre. href="/biz_photos/the-top-gainesville?userid=0-hb63A9uWjR1YIyVMu6rg" class="css-1m051bw">3 photos</a></span></div></div><div class=" margin-b2__09f24__CEMjT border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><p class="comment__09f24__gu0rG css-qgunke"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">This is a generous 4 star review. I&#39;m rounding up from 3.5 because I&#39;m thoroughly impressed with the menu. However, what I ordered wasn&#39;t fantastic. <br><br>I stopped here because of their awesome cocktail menu and the plethora of vegan options. While not a vegan myself, my lady is, so I needed to try out the place for the next time we&#39;re here together. <br><br>I had two of their whiskey drinks-the elder fashioned and the Miles Davis. The elder was, as you probably guessed, their take on an old fashioned. It was okay but it was served in a glass full of ice. Unacceptable, especially when the Miles Davis was served with a single big cube. Why wouldn&#39;t you have served your old fashioned the same way?  Anyway, the Miles Davis-made with coffee pecan bitters and a bock peppercorn simple syrup was the better of the two. Much better. <br><br>For dinner I started with the nachos-all vegan. No sour cream and made with vegan cheese and vegan crumbles. These were good. Far from the best vegan nachos that I&#39;ve had but still good. For my entree I had the San Diego chicken. You&#39;d think a chicken breast stuffed with crab, corn and smoked Gouda in a spicy tomato tequila sauce would have been awesome. It should have been. But it was just good. Nothing wrong with it-but it didn&#39;t stand out like you would think it would. <br><br>The restaurant itself is very dark inside-they do have a patio with some tables but I didn&#39;t see anyone outside. It&#39;s also a bit loud. Not really a romantic date spot but maybe a fun date spot for an average Friday or Saturday or, since this is a college town, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday or Sunday night on the town. <br><br>Anyway, their extensive vegan menu means I&#39;ll be back with the lady. This was a slightly above average meal, but they do deserve extra credit for all of the different dietary restriction options they have. Hoping other items on the menu are more memorable than what I got.</span></p></div><div class=" margin-t3__09f24__riq4X margin-b2__09f24__CEMjT border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><div class=" arrange__09f24__LDfbs gutter-2__09f24__CCmUo layout-wrap__09f24__GEBlv margin-b1__09f24__vaLrm border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><div class=" arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><div class=" photo-container-small__09f24__obhgq border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><div class=" css-1qbt3iv border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><a href="/biz_photos/the-top-gainesville?reviewid=IYlV3RMSPnRirrL5QN_Vlg&amp;select=iJxhWmSUwww6XhE9RuHNKg" class="css-8dlaw4" target="_self"><img class=" css-xlzvdl" src="https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iJxhWmSUwww6XhE9RuHNKg/180s.jpg" alt="Photo of The Top - Gainesville, FL, United States. arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><span class=" css-chan6m">10/9/2019</span><span class=" reviewQualifier__09f24__BbLV6 display--inline__09f24__c6N_k border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><span class=" css-1fnccdf" data-font-weight="semibold">Previous review</span></span></div></div></div></div><div class=" arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"></div></div><div class=" border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><div class=" border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY" role="region" aria-live="polite" id="expander-link-content-26300139-50d4-4807-92cf-bc7b3713a453"><p class="comment__09f24__gu0rG truncated__09f24__PrNXf css-qgunke"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">Stopped at The Top at the tail end of a road trip back from Georgia on a Sunday early afternoon.  I was actually looking forward to things on their full menu, but on Sunday&#39;s, it&#39;s brunch and some items from the regular menu but not much.  The pesto sandwiches and burgers are available, but otherwise, its breakfast.  That wasn&#39;t a problem though since they do have a good brunch menu and plenty of vegan and vegetarian options (important for me, because my love don&#39;t go for meat).<br><br>Let me start with the positives - the breakfast burrito I got was excellent.  I scarfed it down (granted, I was starving) and loved it, even though it had no breakfast meats in it.  I did try to get some breakfast sausage, but they were sold out when I got there (it was 45 minutes before brunch was closed).  Regardless, the burrito was excellent.  And the home fries were even better.  Seriously, were they potatoes or chunks of crack, because daddy loved him some home fries?<br><br>This would be a 4 star meal, maybe 5, if not for the service.  First, we were told 15-20 minute wait, but it was 30.  That in and of itself was not a big deal.  The problem was once we ordered - again, these were breakfast items - it took 40 minutes for it to come out and our server did not come by once.during that time to give us an update, check on us, etc.  All in all, we were here, for brunch, for over an hour and a half.  That&#39;s not acceptable.<br><br>So if service isn&#39;t a big deal to you, then I am sure you&#39;d like it here, and we may even be back our next time in Gainesville if only because of their extensive vegetarian menu, but as good as the food is and as promising as the menu was, the service was enough to turn me off.</span></p></div><button been to The Top a few times, and the vibe is always great. I went with a group of friends to celebrate. I ordered the Seitan Texas Cheesesteak, which was incredibly large and possibly enough for two to eat! My 3 year old daughter quickly grabbed half of the toast, and began to nibble. The texture, and the temperature was great. I managed to finish the sandwich in about half an hour, and overall it had a great flavor and was also priced very reasonably at about $12. <br><br>In terms of portion size and taste, I was very satisfied! I ended up splitting this meal with my toddler, and it was plenty for both of us. We also shared the nachos appetizer with our group, and it was incredibly delicious. class="comment__09f24__gu0rG css-qgunke"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">Waited 1.5 hours on a busy Saturday night -- totally worth it! They have a text message notification wait list, with a link to the site so you can see your place in line. My friend and I went to the barcade across the street to grab a drink while we waited and got back just in time. She told me how great The Top is and she wasn&#39;t wrong. The menu is unique, with amazing vegan options, which was important for me. I got the pecan tofu which was ridiculously good. The service was super friendly. The restaurant has a cool atmosphere, even with the creepy clown aesthetic. photo</a></span></div></div><div class=" margin-b2__09f24__CEMjT border-color--default__09f24__NPAKY"><p class="comment__09f24__gu0rG css-qgunke"><span class=" raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">We were looking for a place to eat outdoors since the weather was nice and the next week is looking cold (for Florida).  We saw the great reviews and stopped here.  The interior is super cool and funky - I would hang here if I were a local.  We were escorted to the equally fun outdoor patio and seated at a raised picnic table along the fence.<br><br>Our server Juan was very friendly and attentive (as was his trainee) - they did a good job of anticipating our needs.  We started off with some beers - must have been happy hour because they were a $1 off the menu price.   Nice.<br><br>I ordered their fried chicken sandwich with a spicy mayo - it was very good and very moist.The bun was soft.  I opted for extra mayo for both the sandwich and fries.  The fries were the only disappointment - just warm and a bit chewy.  My wife had the Caesar salad with pecan crusted tofu it was very tasty.  She liked it alot.<br><br>Overall a great vibe and great food!</span></p></div><div class="
